The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Teen held for sodomy amp; murder

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Oct. 30: A 19-year-old boy was today arrested on charges of sodomising more than 40 ragpickers at Old Delhi Railway Station, including a 13-year-old whom he killed.

 Police arrested Mahfooz Anwar, a pickpocket who had made the station his home for the last eight years, after a witness to the murder came forward and several ragpickers admitted to have been his victims.

 Anwar, alias Pellard Baba, confessed to the crimes during interrogation. He also told the police that he would force the children to distract passengers? attention while he emptied their pockets.

 Ashok, a rickshawpuller at the station, claimed to have seen Anwar murder Indal.

 Indal was found murdered in broad daylight on the footbridge over the station?s platform numbers 3 and 5 on October 21. 

 Deputy commissioner of police, crime branch, Tejender Luthra, said his body bore signs of sexual exploitation.

 Anwar told the police that when he tried to sodomise Indal, he had threatened to expose him. 

 Anwar slit Indal?s throat with a blade and left him to bleed to death.




